An option can be [flatpack][1]. It does not seem to support XML, but you can still marshal/unmarshal flat files. See [Camel documentation][2] for that. 
Also camel [bindy][3] maybe an option.

If you necesairly need to use beanio, you can go for [beanio][4] 3, mentioned in post from Lee Gilbert and wrap it into custom data format to be used with camel.
Example can be:
``` xml
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;com.github.beanio&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;beanio&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;3.0.0.M3&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
